Governor Bill Ritter of Colorado expressed his support for President Obama's proposal to provide tax relief to American families and businesses. He highlighted the impact of the economic downturn on Colorado families, small businesses, ranches, and farms, particularly those who have lost their jobs. Governor Ritter emphasized the need for immediate action to provide tax relief and extend unemployment benefits. He commended President Obama's efforts to compromise with both Republicans and Democrats and stressed the importance of making tough decisions to move the country forward in a bipartisan manner. Governor Ritter urged Congress to act swiftly on this package.